snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Linus, you might not get to this comment being that I'm late to watching this video, but maybe invest in your engineer guy's (I'm so sorry, I forget his name) education just a bit more and have him get some sheet metal forming experience somewhere! When you're forming those heat pipes, I couldn't help but think that if he understood die and punch sizes, springback, bend radii, and bend development/deduction, it would have been a lot less stressful, wasteful (time and material), and more educational for your viewers.
When I worked as a sheet metal manufacturing engineer, we had a lot of custom orders. We made our own dies and punches by laser cutting a pattern of the profiles that we wanted, and put theaded bars through them (nuts on both ends) to secure them together. Then we'd weld all along it to hold them together as a finished product.
